{"title_page": "Solon Robinson", "text_new": "{{Short description|American agriculturalist}}\n{{Refimprove|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n'''Solon Robinson''' (October 21, 1803&nbsp;\u2013 November 3, 1880) was a writer, journalist, agriculturist, and pioneer. He wrote for the ''[[New York Tribune]]'' and ''[[American Agriculturist]]'' and published several books including ''[[Hot Corn]]'', a bestseller.\n\nRobinson was from Connecticut and settled<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.anb.org/view/10.1093/anb/9780198606697.001.0001/anb-9780198606697-e-1001415|title=Robinson, Solon (1803-1880), author, agricultural journalist, and Indiana pioneer &#124; American National Biography|website=www.anb.org|doi=10.1093/anb/9780198606697.001.0001/anb-9780198606697-e-1001415}}</ref> in [[Crown Point, Indiana]] with his family. He formed a [[squatters union]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9yUeZPBAIqwC&pg=PA158&dq=solon+robinson&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjfv8GrwvPkAhVNI6wKHeynCio4ChDoATADegQIARAU#v=onepage&q=solon+robinson&f=false|title=From Pioneering to Persevering: Family Farming in Indiana to 1880|first=Paul|last=Salstrom|date=September 28, 2007|publisher=Purdue University Press|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\nHe was an agriculturist.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/solonrobinsonpio01robi|quote=solon robinson.|title=Solon Robinson, Pioneer and Agriculturist: 1846-1851|first1=Solon|last1=Robinson|first2=Herbert Anthony|last2=Kellar|date=September 28, 1936|publisher=Indiana Historical Bureau|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>\n\nRobinson was one of the prominent reporters at [[Horace Greeley]]'s ''New York Tribune''. He joined the paper in 1852. Robinson wrote about Florida during the [[Reconstruction Era]] convention writing the [[1868 Florida Constitution]]. In 1868, due to poor health, he semi-retired to Jacksonville, Florida. Robinson helped the paper gain popularity in the West and South.\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* ''[[Hot Corn: Life Scenes in New York Illustrated]]'' Dewitt & Davenport 1854, a collection of his articles on personal experiences in the underbelly of New York City\n* ''Mewonitoc; A Story of Western Life, Indian and Doemstic'', a novel serialized in the Weekly Tribune, 1867\n* ''A Northern Farmer on Southern Agriculture'', a serial in the ''Weekly Tribune''\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{BHL author}}\n* {{OL author}}\n* {{Internet Archive author}}\n* {{Worldcat id|lccn-nr92011350}}\n* [https://archives.isl.lib.in.us/repositories/2/resources/238 Solon Robinson collection, Rare Books and Manuscripts, Indiana State Library]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Robinson, Solon}}\n[[Category:1803 births]]\n[[Category:1880 deaths]]\n[[Category:American agriculturalists]]\n[[Category:People from Crown Point, Indiana]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|American agriculturalist}}\n{{Refimprove|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n'''Solon Robinson''' (October 21, 1803&nbsp;\u2013 November 3, 1880) was a writer, journalist, agriculturist, and pioneer. He wrote for the ''[[New York Tribune]]'' and ''[[American Agriculturist]]'' and published several books including ''[[Hot Corn]]'', a bestseller.\n\nRobinson was from Connecticut and settled<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.anb.org/view/10.1093/anb/9780198606697.001.0001/anb-9780198606697-e-1001415|title=Robinson, Solon (1803-1880), author, agricultural journalist, and Indiana pioneer &#124; American National Biography|website=www.anb.org|doi=10.1093/anb/9780198606697.001.0001/anb-9780198606697-e-1001415}}</ref> in [[Crown Point, Indiana]] with his family. He formed a [[squatters union]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9yUeZPBAIqwC&pg=PA158&dq=solon+robinson&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjfv8GrwvPkAhVNI6wKHeynCio4ChDoATADegQIARAU#v=onepage&q=solon+robinson&f=false|title=From Pioneering to Persevering: Family Farming in Indiana to 1880|first=Paul|last=Salstrom|date=September 28, 2007|publisher=Purdue University Press|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\nHe was an agriculturist.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/solonrobinsonpio01robi|quote=solon robinson.|title=Solon Robinson, Pioneer and Agriculturist: 1846-1851|first1=Solon|last1=Robinson|first2=Herbert Anthony|last2=Kellar|date=September 28, 1936|publisher=Indiana Historical Bureau|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>\n\nRobinson was one of the prominent reporters at [[Horace Greeley]]'s ''New York Tribune''. He joined the paper in 1852. Robinson wrote about Florida during the [[Reconstruction Era]] convention writing the [[1868 Florida Constitution]]. In 1868, due to poor health, he semi-retired to Jacksonville, Florida. Robinson helped the paper gain popularity in the West and South.\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* ''[[Hot Corn: Life Scenes in New York Illustrated]]'' Dewitt & Davenport 1854, a collection of his articles on personal experiences in the underbelly of New York City\n* ''Mewonitoc; A Story of Western Life, Indian and Doemstic'', a novel serialized in the Weekly Tribune, 1867\n* ''A Northern Farmer on Southern Agriculture'', a serial in the ''Weekly Tribune''\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{BHL author}}\n* {{OL author}}\n* {{Internet Archive author}}\n* {{Worldcat id|lccn-nr92011350}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Robinson, Solon}}\n[[Category:1803 births]]\n[[Category:1880 deaths]]\n[[Category:American agriculturalists]]\n[[Category:People from Crown Point, Indiana]]\n", "name_user": "Dlawrenceisl", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solon_Robinson"}
{"title_page": "Family law of Singapore", "text_new": "The '''Family law of Singapore''' deals with several family legal issues in [[Singapore]]. It deals with adoptions, divorce, children's issues, division of matrimonial property, personal protection orders, probate and maintenance. The family court in Singapore oversees these legal issues.\nSingapore has two separate and different sets of family law: one for Muslims and the other for everyone else.  Family law for Muslims is codified in the [[Administration of Muslim Law Act]] (AMLA).  Family law for non-Muslims is codified in the [[Women's Charter (Singapore)|Women's Charter]]. The  [[Family Justice Courts of Singapore]] (FJC) handles all family cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.familyjusticecourts.gov.sg/|title=Family Justice Courts|website=www.familyjusticecourts.gov.sg|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n==Divorce==\nBefore a divorce can be granted or considered, the grounds for divorce must be establish.  The recognised grounds are adultery, desertion and unreasonable behaviour.\nIn addition, one party to the marriage has to be domiciled in Singapore or has been staying there for 3 years before one can file for a divorce in Singapore. This applies to both Singapore citizens or foreigners.\n\nTo apply for a divorce, one has to file a writ for divorce, statement of particulars and statement of claim. The reasons for divorce are established in the statement of claim.\nIt is possible to proceed with the divorce proceedings in Singapore without engaging a divorce lawyer. However, the Family Court is not in the position to offer one any advice in this case.\n\nOnce divorce commence, any forms of disputes raised by the defendant will result in the case being referred to a marriage counsellor. If counselling fails, the involved parties will have to file affidavits of evidence and the judge will then determine if the case will proceed as contested or uncontested divorce.\nAt this point, the judge will pass an interim judgement with a 3 months waiting period. This is to give the involved parties one last chance of reconciliation. When that does not happen, the ancillary process will start.\n\nFinally, when the judge deems that the marriage has broken down irretrievably, he will grant the divorce. Only after 3 months from the final decision, then both parties are free to remarry.<ref>[http://sgdivorcelawyer.com/divorce-procedures/ Divorce Procedures in Singapore]. Singapore Divorce Lawyer. Retrieved 21 September 2014.</ref>\n\nTo establish irretrievable breakdown the divorce applicant has to prove one of the following scenarios:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pkwalaw.com/divorce-faqs.html|title=Getting A Divorce In Singapore in 2019 - Fees, Procedures & Process|website=PKWA Law Practice LLC|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-02}}</ref>\n\n* Adultery.\n* Unreasonable behaviour.\n* Desertion for 2 years.\n* Separation for 3 years (and the defendant consents to a divorce).\n* Separation for 4 years.\n\n== Probate ==\nProbate is the process of proving and registering the last [[Will and testament|will or testament]] of a deceased person in the Family Justice Courts. This legal document expresses the deceased person wishes as to how their property is to be distributed and names an [[executor]] who administers the deceased's estate and handles the disposal of their assets and debts. The executor gets this authority by applying to court to obtain a legal document called Grant of Probate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.familyjusticecourts.gov.sg/what-we-do/family-courts/probate|title=Probate|website=www.familyjusticecourts.gov.sg|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\nIf a deceased person did not make a Will, then the family members need to apply for Letter of Administration. The person who will a apply is commonly but not always the surviving spouse or eldest child of the deceased. In this case, the assets are distributed according to the Intestate Succession Act.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pkwalaw.com/news/probate-letters-of-administration-singapore.html|title=Grant of Letters of Administration - How much does it cost?|date=2017-08-28|website=Singapore family law practice|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n== Adoption ==\nAdoption is a legal process, governed under the Adoption of Children Act (ACA) and the Family Court of Singapore is the authority that decides on adoption applications. The Singapore Adoption of Children Act states:\n\n* The parents must be older than 25 years old and at least 21 years older than the adoption child. \n* Adoptive parent must not be more than 50 years older than the child.\n* Parent should have sound mental health.\n* The child must be under 21 years old and a Singapore resident. A foreign-born child may be adopted, but will need to get a Dependant\u2019s Pass from the [[Ministry of Community Development, Youth and Sports|Ministry of Community Development, Youth and Sport]] (MCYS).\n* Both married couples and singles can adopt a child. However, a single male is not allowed to adopt a girl unless special circumstances exist.\n* Parents must be Singaporean citizens or permanent residents, or hold passes which the Family Justice Courts deem fit to qualify them as residents in Singapore.\n\nThese rules may be waived if special circumstances justify the adoption.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sg.theasianparent.com/want-to-adopt-a-child|title=Adoption In Singapore - Adopt A Child In Singapore {{!}} theAsianparent|last=Mahtani|first=Roshni|date=2016-01-05|website=sg.theasianparent.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n== Family Law firms ==\nFamily law firms of Singapore in alphabetical order:\n* [https://www.gjclaw.com.sg/ Gloria James-Civetta & Co]\n* [[Allen & Gledhill|Allen & Gledhill LLP]]\n* [[Donaldson & Burkinshaw|Donaldson & Burkinshaw LLP]]\n* [[PWKA|PKWA Law Practice LLC]]\n* [[Rajah & Tann|Rajah & Tann Singapore LLP]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090417072035/http://app.subcourts.gov.sg/family/page.aspx?pageid=12433 Family Court of Singapore]\n* [https://www.singaporedivorcelawyer.com.sg/ Singapore Divorce Lawyer]\n*[https://www.sgdivorcelawyer.sg/ Singapore Family Law Firm]\n*[https://www.msf.gov.sg/Adoption/Pages/default.aspx Ministry of Social and Family development]\n\n{{Law of Singapore}}\n\n[[Category:Family law in Singapore| ]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Family law of Singapore''' deals with several family legal issues in [[Singapore]]. It deals with adoptions, divorce, children's issues, division of matrimonial property, personal protection orders, probate and maintenance. The family court in Singapore oversees these legal issues.\nSingapore has two separate and different sets of family law: one for Muslims and the other for everyone else.  Family law for Muslims is codified in the [[Administration of Muslim Law Act]] (AMLA).  Family law for non-Muslims is codified in the [[Women's Charter (Singapore)|Women's Charter]]. The  [[Family Justice Courts of Singapore]] (FJC) handles all family cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.familyjusticecourts.gov.sg/|title=Family Justice Courts|website=www.familyjusticecourts.gov.sg|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n==Divorce==\nBefore a divorce can be granted or considered, the grounds for divorce must be establish.  The recognised grounds are adultery, desertion and unreasonable behaviour.\nIn addition, one party to the marriage has to be domiciled in Singapore or has been staying there for 3 years before one can file for a divorce in Singapore. This applies to both Singapore citizens or foreigners.\n\nTo apply for a divorce, one has to file a writ for divorce, statement of particulars and statement of claim. The reasons for divorce are established in the statement of claim.\nIt is possible to proceed with the divorce proceedings in Singapore without engaging a divorce lawyer. However, the Family Court is not in the position to offer one any advice in this case.\n\nOnce divorce commence, any forms of disputes raised by the defendant will result in the case being referred to a marriage counsellor. If counselling fails, the involved parties will have to file affidavits of evidence and the judge will then determine if the case will proceed as contested or uncontested divorce.\nAt this point, the judge will pass an interim judgement with a 3 months waiting period. This is to give the involved parties one last chance of reconciliation. When that does not happen, the ancillary process will start.\n\nFinally, when the judge deems that the marriage has broken down irretrievably, he will grant the divorce. Only after 3 months from the final decision, then both parties are free to remarry.<ref>[http://sgdivorcelawyer.com/divorce-procedures/ Divorce Procedures in Singapore]. Singapore Divorce Lawyer. Retrieved 21 September 2014.</ref>\n\nTo establish irretrievable breakdown the divorce applicant has to prove one of the following scenarios:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pkwalaw.com/divorce-faqs.html|title=Getting A Divorce In Singapore in 2019 - Fees, Procedures & Process|website=PKWA Law Practice LLC|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-02}}</ref>\n\n* Adultery.\n* Unreasonable behaviour.\n* Desertion for 2 years.\n* Separation for 3 years (and the defendant consents to a divorce).\n* Separation for 4 years.\n\n== Probate ==\nProbate is the process of proving and registering the last [[Will and testament|will or testament]] of a deceased person in the Family Justice Courts. This legal document expresses the deceased person wishes as to how their property is to be distributed and names an [[executor]] who administers the deceased's estate and handles the disposal of their assets and debts. The executor gets this authority by applying to court to obtain a legal document called Grant of Probate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.familyjusticecourts.gov.sg/what-we-do/family-courts/probate|title=Probate|website=www.familyjusticecourts.gov.sg|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\nIf a deceased person did not make a Will, then the family members need to apply for Letter of Administration. The person who will a apply is commonly but not always the surviving spouse or eldest child of the deceased. In this case, the assets are distributed according to the Intestate Succession Act.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pkwalaw.com/news/probate-letters-of-administration-singapore.html|title=Grant of Letters of Administration - How much does it cost?|date=2017-08-28|website=Singapore family law practice|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n== Adoption ==\nAdoption is a legal process, governed under the Adoption of Children Act (ACA) and the Family Court of Singapore is the authority that decides on adoption applications. The Singapore Adoption of Children Act states:\n\n* The parents must be older than 25 years old and at least 21 years older than the adoption child. \n* Adoptive parent must not be more than 50 years older than the child.\n* Parent should have sound mental health.\n* The child must be under 21 years old and a Singapore resident. A foreign-born child may be adopted, but will need to get a Dependant\u2019s Pass from the [[Ministry of Community Development, Youth and Sports|Ministry of Community Development, Youth and Sport]] (MCYS).\n* Both married couples and singles can adopt a child. However, a single male is not allowed to adopt a girl unless special circumstances exist.\n* Parents must be Singaporean citizens or permanent residents, or hold passes which the Family Justice Courts deem fit to qualify them as residents in Singapore.\n\nThese rules may be waived if special circumstances justify the adoption.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sg.theasianparent.com/want-to-adopt-a-child|title=Adoption In Singapore - Adopt A Child In Singapore {{!}} theAsianparent|last=Mahtani|first=Roshni|date=2016-01-05|website=sg.theasianparent.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n== Family Law firms ==\nFamily law firms of Singapore in alphabetical order:\n\n* [[Allen & Gledhill|Allen & Gledhill LLP]]\n* [[Donaldson & Burkinshaw|Donaldson & Burkinshaw LLP]]\n* [[PWKA|PKWA Law Practice LLC]]\n* [[Rajah & Tann|Rajah & Tann Singapore LLP]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090417072035/http://app.subcourts.gov.sg/family/page.aspx?pageid=12433 Family Court of Singapore]\n* [https://www.singaporedivorcelawyer.com.sg/ Singapore Divorce Lawyer]\n*[https://www.sgdivorcelawyer.sg/ Singapore Family Law Firm]\n*[https://www.msf.gov.sg/Adoption/Pages/default.aspx Ministry of Social and Family development]\n\n{{Law of Singapore}}\n\n[[Category:Family law in Singapore| ]]\n", "name_user": "202.142.80.47", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eFamily Law firms)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Family_law_of_Singapore"}
{"title_page": "You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name     =\n| cover    =\n| alt      =\n| type     = Song\n| artist   = [[Miley Cyrus|Hannah Montana]]\n| album    = [[Hannah Montana: The Movie (soundtrack)|Hannah Montana: The Movie]]\n| released = April 2, 2009\n| format   = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded = 2008\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    = {{hlist|[[Country pop]]|[[pop rock]]}}\n| length   = 3:44\n| label    = [[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n| writer   = {{hlist|[[Taylor Swift]]|[[Martin Johnson (vocalist)|Martin Johnson]]}}\n| producer = [[Matthew Gerrard]]\n}}\n\n\"'''You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home'''\" is a [[country pop]] song written for the 2009 film ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]''. The song is performed by [[Hannah Montana]], a character [[Miley Cyrus]] portrays in the film. The song was written by American singer-songwriter [[Taylor Swift]] and American singer [[Martin Johnson (musician)|Martin Johnson]]. A [[karaoke]] version of the song is available in [[Hannah Montana: The Movie (soundtrack)#Karaoke series|the soundtrack's karaoke series]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://disneymusic.disney.go.com/albums/karaokehannahmovie.html|title=Disney's Karaoke Series: Hannah Montana The Movie|work=[[Walt Disney Records]]|accessdate=November 6, 2009|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]}}</ref> The song is musically [[country pop]] and [[pop rock]]. Lyrically, the track is about staying grounded and going back to one's roots.\n\nThe song received critical success for its use in the film. \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" was met with average-to-low commercial outcomes for Cyrus in several countries, compared to those of her previous efforts as Montana. It reached its highest international peak in the [[Canadian Hot 100]], at number thirty-six. The song received a music video to coincide with the home release of ''Hannah Montana: The Movie''.\n\n==Development==\nSinger-songwriter [[Taylor Swift]] became involved with ''Hannah Montana: The Movie'' when filmmakers emailed her specifically to request the use of her music in the film. Swift agreed to make a [[cameo appearance]] in the film to sing \"[[Crazier (Taylor Swift song)|Crazier]]\" as well as to co-write a song with [[Boys Like Girls]] lead singer [[Martin Johnson (vocalist)|Martin Johnson]].<ref name=\"prod\">{{cite web|url=http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2009/hanna_montana/notes.pdf |title=Hannah Montana The Movie Production Notes |work=[[Walt Disney Pictures]] |publisher=VisualHollywood.com |accessdate=October 16, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5lNC4Dlzi?url=http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2009/hanna_montana/notes.pdf |archivedate=November 18, 2009 }}</ref> In an interview with [[MTV]], Johnson described working with Swift:\n{{quote|\"She's awesome. She's one of the most talented songwriters to work with, if not, the best. For such a young girl, she's so creative and spot-on. She knows the audience, she truly understands the kind of pop music that is from the heart and done in a tasteful way. She knows ways to make things pop and also make you feel it at the same time. We wrote a bunch of songs together and it was a lot of fun.\"<ref name=\"interview\">{{Cite interview|url=http://www.mtvasia.com/News/200908/25018372.html |subjectlink=Martin Johnson (vocalist) |first=Martin |last=Johnson |title=Boys Like Girls Interview: Love Drunk and In High Spirits |date=August 25, 2009 |accessdate=November 28, 2009 |interviewer=[[MTV]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091001020530/http://www.mtvasia.com/News/200908/25018372.html |archivedate=October 1, 2009 }}</ref>}}\n\n\"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" is used as the closing number of ''Hannah Montana: The Movie''. In the film, Cyrus performs as popstar Hannah Montana onstage at an outdoor fundraiser to save her hometown's treasured park from developers. More than 2,000 [[Extra (actor)|extras]] were used to film the scene.<ref name=\"prod\" />\n\n==Composition==\n{{listen\n|pos=right\n|filename=findwaybackhomesamp.ogg\n|title=\"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" (2009)\n|description=A sample of Hannah Montana's \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\". \n|format=[[Ogg]]\n}}\n\"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\", according to [[AllMusic]], embodies the album's theme of merging [[Country music|country]] and [[pop music]].<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r1479519|pure_url=yes}}|work=[[AllMusic]]|publisher=[[Macrovision Corporation]]|accessdate=November 6, 2009|title=Hannah Montana: The Movie [Soundtrack<nowiki>]</nowiki> > Review|first=Heather|last=Phares}}</ref> It is set in [[common time]] with a fast rock [[tempo]] of 160 [[beats per minute]].<ref name=\"sheet\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0076644|title=Hannah Montana \u2013 You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home She Music (Digital Download)|work=MusicNotes.com|publisher=[[Alfred Publishing]]|accessdate=November 6, 2009}}</ref> The song is written in the key of [[E\u266d major]].<ref name=\"sheet\" /> Cyrus' vocals span one [[octave]], from B\u266d<sub>3</sub> to B<sub>4</sub>.<ref name=\"sheet\" /> The song has the following [[chord progression]], E\u266d5\u2014D5\u2014E\u266d5.<ref name=\"sheet\" /> Like the film, the lyrics discuss importance of one's roots.<ref name=\"prod\" /> Warren Truitt of [[About.com]] believed it conveyed \"the sentiment that even pop stars find safe haven in their home town\".<ref name=\"tophmsongs\">{{cite web|url=http://kidsmusic.about.com/od/toppicks/tp/top10hannahmontanasongs.htm|title=Music by Miley Cyrus' Alter Ego, Hannah Montana|first=Warren|last=Truitt|work=[[About.com]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|accessdate=May 18, 2010}}</ref>\nThe first few lyrics of the song's chorus are almost identical to the opening verse in [[Hilary Duff]]'s song \"[[So Yesterday]]\", which was released in 2003.\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe song received positive reviews from critics. Simon Weaving of Screenwize.com said the film's conflicts are \"mostly expressed in the simple, sugared lyrics of a series of pop hits that seamlessly find their way into the story\u2013 including '[[The Best of Both Worlds (song)|The Best of Both Worlds]]' and 'You\u2019ll Always Find a Way Back Home'.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.screenwize.com/archives/431 |title=Review of \"Hannah Montana: the Movie\" |first=Simon |last=Weaving |publisher=ScreenWize.com |accessdate=November 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712143158/http://www.screenwize.com/archives/431 |archivedate=July 12, 2009 }}</ref> James Plath of Dvdtown.com described the song as being \"integrated pretty well into the narrative\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtown.com/review/hannah-montana-the-movie/blu-ray/7250 |title=Hannah Montana: The Movie (Blu-ray) |date=August 22, 2009 |publisher=DVDTown.com |first=James |last=Plath |accessdate=November 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090826202032/http://www.dvdtown.com/review/hannah-montana-the-movie/blu-ray/7250 |archivedate=August 26, 2009 }}</ref> Peter Canavese of Grouncho Reviews said \"the story makes way  for [...] 'You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home'\", which would attract \"the film's target audience of pre-teen girls\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.grouchoreviews.com/reviews/3519|title=Hannah Montana: The Movie|first=Peter|last=Canavese|publisher=Grouncho Reviews|accessdate=November 28, 2009}}</ref> Warren of Truitt of About.com listed the song as the third best song by Hannah Montana.<ref name=\"tophmsongs\" /> The song was included on the [[short list]] for [[Academy Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]] at the [[82nd Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i5a83a539b5b67442326fd65b32cf3abd|archive-url=https://archive.is/20100331200102/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i5a83a539b5b67442326fd65b32cf3abd|url-status=dead|archive-date=March 31, 2010|title=Academy unveils original song candidates|work=The Hollywood Reporter|publisher=Trade Entertainment|date=December 16, 2009|author= Kilday, Gregg|accessdate=December 19, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\nThe song made its debut on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number eighty-seven on the week ending April 11, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/269058/lady-gaga-scores-hot-100-milestone-with-poker-face|title=Lady GaGa Scores Hot 100 Milestone With 'Poker Face'|first=Ayala|last=Ben-Yehuda|author2=Silvio Pietroluongo |date=April 2, 2009|location=[[Los Angeles]] and [[New York City]]|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Nielsen Business Media, Inc]]|accessdate=November 27, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"acharts\">{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/song/42830|title=Hannah Montana \u2013 You'll Always Find Your Way back Home \u2013 Music Charts|publisher=aCharts.us|accessdate=November 27, 2006}}</ref> \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" fell one spot to number eighty-eight in the following week,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/268913/chart-beat-rascal-flatts-miley-cyrus-eminem-jason-mraz |title=Chart Beat: Rascal Flatts, Miley Cyrus, Eminem, Jason Mraz |first=Gary |last=Trust |author2=Keith Caulfield |date=April 16, 2009 |location=Los Angeles and New York City |work=Billboard |publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |accessdate=November 27, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130205030749/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/268913/chart-beat-rascal-flatts-miley-cyrus-eminem-jason-mraz |archivedate=February 5, 2013 }}</ref> but on the week ending May 2, 2009 it reached its peak on the Hot 100 at number eighty-one due to digital downloads that placed it at number fifty-two on [[Hot Digital Songs]].<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/news/eminem-green-day-make-big-hot-100-debuts-1003965853.story#/song/movie-soundtrack/you-ll-always-find-your-way-back-home/12922526|title=You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home|work=Billboard|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc|accessdate=November 27, 2009}}</ref> In the [[Canadian Hot 100]], \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" debuted at eighty-eight on the week ending April 11, 2009 and reached its peak at number seventy-six on the week ending May 2, 2009.<ref name=\"acharts\" /><ref name=\"billboard\" />\n\n==Music video==\nA promotional music video for \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" was filmed in correlation to the ''Hannah Montana: The Movie'' soundtrack.<ref name=\"miley sessions\">{{cite web|url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/hannah-montana/videos/view/youll-always-find-your-way-back-home-the-miley-sessions--208575477 |title=You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home (The Miley Sessions) |work=[[Disney.com]] |publisher=[[Yahoo! Music]] |accessdate=November 27, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090530182153/http://new.music.yahoo.com/hannah-montana/videos/view/youll-always-find-your-way-back-home-the-miley-sessions--208575477 |archivedate=May 30, 2009 }}</ref> The video, part of a series of promotional videos titled ''The Miley Sessions'', was released in March 2009 on [[Disney.com]] and features Cyrus singing in a vacant [[recording studio]].\n\nAn excerpt from ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]'' premiered as the song's music video in August 2009 on [[Disney Channel]] to promote the home release of the film. The video begins with Cyrus and her backup dancers atop a stage in a crowded outdoor concert. Cyrus is dressed as Hannah Montana and is wearing a [[Suit (clothing)|business suit]]. As Cyrus begins singing, she and the dancers engage in intricate choreography. The video then transitions to a clip from ''Hannah Montana: The Movie'' in which Cyrus' character is getting down from a private airplane. The video continues to alternate between Cyrus performing and more film clips; scenes include Stewart taking off her Hannah Montana wig and interacting with Travis Body, her love interest in the film, portrayed by actor [[Lucas Till]]. Midway through the video, Cyrus and her dancers exit the stage through a back door and instantly enter sporting [[Western wear|western clothing]] with Cyrus in a western teal button up shirt, a checkered red and white table cloth with purple ruffles pettiskirt or a [[petticoat]], and [[cowboy boots]]. Meanwhile, as the video ends, it shows that Miley wakes up and realizes (after the earlier events from the film) it's just a dream, with Jackson's car driving through the road, and the video ends.\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"center\"|Chart (2009)\n!align=\"center\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| [[Canadian Hot 100]]<ref name=\"billboard\" />\n|align=\"center\"|76\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| U.S. [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref name=\"billboard\" />\n|align=\"center\"|81\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://tv.disney.go.com/disneychannel/hannahmontana/ The official website of ''Hannah Montana'']\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091129014649/http://disneydvd.disney.go.com/hannah-montana-the-movie.html The official website of ''Hannah Montana: The Movie'']\n* {{MetroLyrics song|hannah-montana|youll-always-find-your-way-back-home}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Hannah Montana singles}}\n{{Taylor Swift songs}}\n\n{{good article}}\n\n[[Category:2009 songs]]\n[[Category:American country music songs]]\n[[Category:American pop rock songs]]\n[[Category:Hannah Montana songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Taylor Swift]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Martin Johnson (musician)]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Records singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name     =\n| cover    =\n| alt      =\n| type     = Song\n| artist   = [[Miley Cyrus|Hannah Montana]]\n| album    = [[Hannah Montana: The Movie (soundtrack)|Hannah Montana: The Movie]]\n| released = April 2, 2009\n| format   = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded = 2008\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    = {{hlist|[[Country pop]]|[[pop rock]]}}\n| length   = 3:44\n| label    = [[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n| writer   = {{hlist|[[Taylor Swift]]|[[Martin Johnson (vocalist)|Martin Johnson]]}}\n| producer = [[Matthew Gerrard]]\n}}\n\n\"'''You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home'''\" is a [[country pop]] song written for the 2009 film ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]''. The song is performed by [[Hannah Montana]], a character [[Miley Cyrus]] portrays in the film. The song was written by American singer-songwriter [[Taylor Swift]] and American singer [[Martin Johnson (musician)|Martin Johnson]]. A [[karaoke]] version of the song is available in [[Hannah Montana: The Movie (soundtrack)#Karaoke series|the soundtrack's karaoke series]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://disneymusic.disney.go.com/albums/karaokehannahmovie.html|title=Disney's Karaoke Series: Hannah Montana The Movie|work=[[Walt Disney Records]]|accessdate=November 6, 2009|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]}}</ref> The song is musically [[country pop]] and [[pop rock]]. Lyrically, the track is about staying grounded and going back to one's roots.\n\nThe song received critical success for its use in the film. \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" was met with average-to-low commercial outcomes for Cyrus in several countries, compared to those of her previous efforts as Montana. It reached its highest international peak in the [[Canadian Hot 100]], at number thirty-six. The song received a music video to coincide with the home release of ''Hannah Montana: The Movie''.\n\n==Development==\nSinger-songwriter [[Taylor Swift]] became involved with ''Hannah Montana: The Movie'' when filmmakers emailed her specifically to request the use of her music in the film. Swift agreed to make a [[cameo appearance]] in the film to sing \"[[Crazier (Taylor Swift song)|Crazier]]\" as well as to co-write a song with [[Boys Like Girls]] lead singer [[Martin Johnson (vocalist)|Martin Johnson]].<ref name=\"prod\">{{cite web|url=http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2009/hanna_montana/notes.pdf |title=Hannah Montana The Movie Production Notes |work=[[Walt Disney Pictures]] |publisher=VisualHollywood.com |accessdate=October 16, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5lNC4Dlzi?url=http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2009/hanna_montana/notes.pdf |archivedate=November 18, 2009 }}</ref> In an interview with [[MTV]], Johnson described working with Swift:\n{{quote|\"She's awesome. She's one of the most talented songwriters to work with, if not, the best. For such a young girl, she's so creative and spot-on. She knows the audience, she truly understands the kind of pop music that is from the heart and done in a tasteful way. She knows ways to make things pop and also make you feel it at the same time. We wrote a bunch of songs together and it was a lot of fun.\"<ref name=\"interview\">{{Cite interview|url=http://www.mtvasia.com/News/200908/25018372.html |subjectlink=Martin Johnson (vocalist) |first=Martin |last=Johnson |title=Boys Like Girls Interview: Love Drunk and In High Spirits |date=August 25, 2009 |accessdate=November 28, 2009 |interviewer=[[MTV]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091001020530/http://www.mtvasia.com/News/200908/25018372.html |archivedate=October 1, 2009 }}</ref>}}\n\n\"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" is used as the closing number of ''Hannah Montana: The Movie''. In the film, Cyrus performs as popstar Hannah Montana onstage at an outdoor fundraiser to save her hometown's treasured park from developers. More than 2,000 [[Extra (actor)|extras]] were used to film the scene.<ref name=\"prod\" />\n\n==Composition==\n{{listen\n|pos=right\n|filename=findwaybackhomesamp.ogg\n|title=\"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" (2009)\n|description=A sample of Hannah Montana's \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\". \n|format=[[Ogg]]\n}}\n\"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\", according to [[Allmusic]], embodies the album's theme of merging [[Country music|country]] and [[pop music]].<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r1479519|pure_url=yes}}|work=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=[[Macrovision Corporation]]|accessdate=November 6, 2009|title=Hannah Montana: The Movie [Soundtrack<nowiki>]</nowiki> > Review|first=Heather|last=Phares}}</ref> It is set in [[common time]] with a fast rock [[tempo]] of 160 [[beats per minute]].<ref name=\"sheet\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0076644|title=Hannah Montana \u2013 You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home She Music (Digital Download)|work=MusicNotes.com|publisher=[[Alfred Publishing]]|accessdate=November 6, 2009}}</ref> The song is written in the key of [[E\u266d major]].<ref name=\"sheet\" /> Cyrus' vocals span one [[octave]], from B\u266d<sub>3</sub> to B<sub>4</sub>.<ref name=\"sheet\" /> The song has the following [[chord progression]], E\u266d5\u2014D5\u2014E\u266d5.<ref name=\"sheet\" /> Like the film, the lyrics discuss importance of one's roots.<ref name=\"prod\" /> Warren Truitt of [[About.com]] believed it conveyed \"the sentiment that even pop stars find safe haven in their home town\".<ref name=\"tophmsongs\">{{cite web|url=http://kidsmusic.about.com/od/toppicks/tp/top10hannahmontanasongs.htm|title=Music by Miley Cyrus' Alter Ego, Hannah Montana|first=Warren|last=Truitt|work=[[About.com]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|accessdate=May 18, 2010}}</ref>\nThe first few lyrics of the song's chorus are almost identical to the opening verse in [[Hilary Duff]]'s song \"[[So Yesterday]]\", which was released in 2003.\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe song received positive reviews from critics. Simon Weaving of Screenwize.com said the film's conflicts are \"mostly expressed in the simple, sugared lyrics of a series of pop hits that seamlessly find their way into the story\u2013 including '[[The Best of Both Worlds (song)|The Best of Both Worlds]]' and 'You\u2019ll Always Find a Way Back Home'.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.screenwize.com/archives/431 |title=Review of \"Hannah Montana: the Movie\" |first=Simon |last=Weaving |publisher=ScreenWize.com |accessdate=November 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712143158/http://www.screenwize.com/archives/431 |archivedate=July 12, 2009 }}</ref> James Plath of Dvdtown.com described the song as being \"integrated pretty well into the narrative\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtown.com/review/hannah-montana-the-movie/blu-ray/7250 |title=Hannah Montana: The Movie (Blu-ray) |date=August 22, 2009 |publisher=DVDTown.com |first=James |last=Plath |accessdate=November 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090826202032/http://www.dvdtown.com/review/hannah-montana-the-movie/blu-ray/7250 |archivedate=August 26, 2009 }}</ref> Peter Canavese of Grouncho Reviews said \"the story makes way  for [...] 'You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home'\", which would attract \"the film's target audience of pre-teen girls\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.grouchoreviews.com/reviews/3519|title=Hannah Montana: The Movie|first=Peter|last=Canavese|publisher=Grouncho Reviews|accessdate=November 28, 2009}}</ref> Warren of Truitt of About.com listed the song as the third best song by Hannah Montana.<ref name=\"tophmsongs\" /> The song was included on the [[short list]] for [[Academy Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]] at the [[82nd Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i5a83a539b5b67442326fd65b32cf3abd|archive-url=https://archive.is/20100331200102/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i5a83a539b5b67442326fd65b32cf3abd|url-status=dead|archive-date=March 31, 2010|title=Academy unveils original song candidates|work=The Hollywood Reporter|publisher=Trade Entertainment|date=December 16, 2009|author= Kilday, Gregg|accessdate=December 19, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\nThe song made its debut on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number eighty-seven on the week ending April 11, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/269058/lady-gaga-scores-hot-100-milestone-with-poker-face|title=Lady GaGa Scores Hot 100 Milestone With 'Poker Face'|first=Ayala|last=Ben-Yehuda|author2=Silvio Pietroluongo |date=April 2, 2009|location=[[Los Angeles]] and [[New York City]]|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Nielsen Business Media, Inc]]|accessdate=November 27, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"acharts\">{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/song/42830|title=Hannah Montana \u2013 You'll Always Find Your Way back Home \u2013 Music Charts|publisher=aCharts.us|accessdate=November 27, 2006}}</ref> \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" fell one spot to number eighty-eight in the following week,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/268913/chart-beat-rascal-flatts-miley-cyrus-eminem-jason-mraz |title=Chart Beat: Rascal Flatts, Miley Cyrus, Eminem, Jason Mraz |first=Gary |last=Trust |author2=Keith Caulfield |date=April 16, 2009 |location=Los Angeles and New York City |work=Billboard |publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |accessdate=November 27, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130205030749/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/268913/chart-beat-rascal-flatts-miley-cyrus-eminem-jason-mraz |archivedate=February 5, 2013 }}</ref> but on the week ending May 2, 2009 it reached its peak on the Hot 100 at number eighty-one due to digital downloads that placed it at number fifty-two on [[Hot Digital Songs]].<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/news/eminem-green-day-make-big-hot-100-debuts-1003965853.story#/song/movie-soundtrack/you-ll-always-find-your-way-back-home/12922526|title=You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home|work=Billboard|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc|accessdate=November 27, 2009}}</ref> In the [[Canadian Hot 100]], \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" debuted at eighty-eight on the week ending April 11, 2009 and reached its peak at number seventy-six on the week ending May 2, 2009.<ref name=\"acharts\" /><ref name=\"billboard\" />\n\n==Music video==\nA promotional music video for \"You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home\" was filmed in correlation to the ''Hannah Montana: The Movie'' soundtrack.<ref name=\"miley sessions\">{{cite web|url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/hannah-montana/videos/view/youll-always-find-your-way-back-home-the-miley-sessions--208575477 |title=You'll Always Find Your Way Back Home (The Miley Sessions) |work=[[Disney.com]] |publisher=[[Yahoo! Music]] |accessdate=November 27, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090530182153/http://new.music.yahoo.com/hannah-montana/videos/view/youll-always-find-your-way-back-home-the-miley-sessions--208575477 |archivedate=May 30, 2009 }}</ref> The video, part of a series of promotional videos titled ''The Miley Sessions'', was released in March 2009 on [[Disney.com]] and features Cyrus singing in a vacant [[recording studio]].\n\nAn excerpt from ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]'' premiered as the song's music video in August 2009 on [[Disney Channel]] to promote the home release of the film. The video begins with Cyrus and her backup dancers atop a stage in a crowded outdoor concert. Cyrus is dressed as Hannah Montana and is wearing a [[Suit (clothing)|business suit]]. As Cyrus begins singing, she and the dancers engage in intricate choreography. The video then transitions to a clip from ''Hannah Montana: The Movie'' in which Cyrus' character is getting down from a private airplane. The video continues to alternate between Cyrus performing and more film clips; scenes include Stewart taking off her Hannah Montana wig and interacting with Travis Body, her love interest in the film, portrayed by actor [[Lucas Till]]. Midway through the video, Cyrus and her dancers exit the stage through a back door and instantly enter sporting [[Western wear|western clothing]] with Cyrus in a western teal button up shirt, a checkered red and white table cloth with purple ruffles pettiskirt or a [[petticoat]], and [[cowboy boots]]. Meanwhile, as the video ends, it shows that Miley wakes up and realizes (after the earlier events from the film) it's just a dream, with Jackson's car driving through the road, and the video ends.\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"center\"|Chart (2009)\n!align=\"center\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| [[Canadian Hot 100]]<ref name=\"billboard\" />\n|align=\"center\"|76\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| U.S. [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref name=\"billboard\" />\n|align=\"center\"|81\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://tv.disney.go.com/disneychannel/hannahmontana/ The official website of ''Hannah Montana'']\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091129014649/http://disneydvd.disney.go.com/hannah-montana-the-movie.html The official website of ''Hannah Montana: The Movie'']\n* {{MetroLyrics song|hannah-montana|youll-always-find-your-way-back-home}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Hannah Montana singles}}\n{{Taylor Swift songs}}\n\n{{good article}}\n\n[[Category:2009 songs]]\n[[Category:American country music songs]]\n[[Category:American pop rock songs]]\n[[Category:Hannah Montana songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Taylor Swift]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Martin Johnson (musician)]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Records singles]]\n", "name_user": "Danionek", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eComposition", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/You%27ll_Always_Find_Your_Way_Back_Home"}
